The Wedding of Archduke Georg of Austria, the second son of Archduke Otto and Archduchess Regina von Habsburg, and Duchess Eilika of Oldenburg, daughter of Duke Hohann of Oldenburg and Countess Ilka of Ortenburg, at St. Stephen’s Basilica in Budapest on this day in 1997, following a Gala. The couple have three children: Archduchess Sophie, Archduchess Ilka and Archduke Károly-Konstantin and Archduke Georg serves Hungary’s Ambassador to France.

Embed from Getty ImagesEmbed from Getty ImagesEmbed from Getty ImagesEmbed from Getty ImagesEmbed from Getty Images

Royal Guests and Relatives included King Hassan II of Morocco, King Felipe VI of Spain (then the Prince of Asturias), Prince Albert of Monaco, and the Duke and Duchess of Braganza alongside members of the extended Habsburg and Oldenburg Families and numerous European Royalty and Nobility, including Princess Gloria von Thurn and Taxis.
